Summary
In this project, I conducted an in-depth review of file and directory permissions on a Linux system. I evaluated existing access settings and corrected them to align with the least privilege principle.
By tightening access controls, the overall attack surface was reduced — minimizing the risk of unauthorized access or modification. This work demonstrates how proactive permission management plays a critical role in maintaining security within an enterprise environment.
